02:39.291 --> 02:42.293
My husband and I scrimped
and saved for so many years.

02:43.477 --> 02:45.644
We did our best to build a nest egg

02:45.679 --> 02:48.413
so that we wouldn't be a
burden to our family.

02:48.449 --> 02:51.950
After Ronald passed, I moved to
an assisted-living facility...

02:51.985 --> 02:53.618
a nice place.

02:54.440 --> 02:56.907
They told me they'd take care of everything,

02:56.947 --> 03:00.748
but then, one day, they said
all my money was gone.

03:00.784 --> 03:02.383
How could that be?

03:02.419 --> 03:04.846
Where did it all go?

03:04.898 --> 03:06.532
Jimmy: If you or a loved one

03:06.554 --> 03:08.988
is a resident of a Sandpiper
crossing facility or

03:09.024 --> 03:12.125
- other associated retirement community...
- Jesus. You used your own voice?

03:12.160 --> 03:13.893
Strictly to save money.

03:13.928 --> 03:15.161
- All in, the whole thing cost...
- Just...

03:15.939 --> 03:20.800
Call the law offices of
Davis & Main at 505-242-7700.

03:20.843 --> 03:24.129
That's 505-242-7700.

03:24.134 --> 03:25.601
[Sighs]

03:25.636 --> 03:30.472
The production costs... $647, all in.

03:30.507 --> 03:34.610
The one single airing was
a $700 ad buy, so dirt-cheap.

03:34.645 --> 03:36.411
You think this is about money?

03:36.447 --> 03:38.480
You think that's what this is about?

03:38.515 --> 03:41.249
I'm just trying to offer
complete information here.

03:41.285 --> 03:43.752
Now, this one airing...
it was an experiment,

03:43.787 --> 03:45.520
and as such, by any measure, a success.

03:45.556 --> 03:47.255
You keep using the word "experiment"

03:47.291 --> 03:49.157
like you're ‭the goddamned Wright Brothers.

03:49.193 --> 03:51.259
When exactly were you gonna
tell us about this experiment?

03:51.295 --> 03:52.494
Today.

03:52.529 --> 03:53.962
This morning.

03:53.998 --> 03:55.931
I-I admit, I got a little ahead of myself,

03:55.966 --> 03:57.199
a little... Exuberant.

03:57.234 --> 03:59.034
And for that, I apologize.

03:59.069 --> 04:01.603
But the headline here is... I think...

04:01.639 --> 04:05.207
We've gotten nearly 200 phone
calls since this one airing.

04:05.242 --> 04:08.343
Cliff, since you and I spoke
last night, 72 more.

04:08.379 --> 04:10.045
[Telephone rings in distance]

04:10.080 --> 04:13.115
You hear that? Right there...
That's the sound of victory.

04:13.150 --> 04:14.650
Jimmy, stop selling.

04:14.685 --> 04:17.351
And don't act like
‭you don't see the problem here.

04:17.387 --> 04:19.387
I don't.

04:19.423 --> 04:20.956
[Scoffs] You cut us out.

04:20.991 --> 04:23.225
You did an end run around us.

04:23.260 --> 04:25.193
Exuberance is no excuse.

04:25.229 --> 04:26.795
Cliff. [Sighs]

04:26.830 --> 04:29.965
Client outreach is my department.

04:30.000 --> 04:31.566
Now, you told me that from day one.

04:31.602 --> 04:33.502
Jimmy, if I put you in charge
of payroll, would that mean

04:33.537 --> 04:35.737
I'd be okay with you giving
everyone a million-dollar bonus?

04:35.773 --> 04:38.373
You and I did discuss the
possibility of a commercial.

04:38.409 --> 04:40.142
The possibility in the abstract,

04:40.177 --> 04:43.145
for a grand total of 30 seconds
when I was halfway out the door.

04:43.180 --> 04:44.546
[Sighs]

04:44.581 --> 04:46.181
I guess... I thought I heard enthusiasm,

04:46.216 --> 04:47.983
so I... I took some initiative.

04:48.018 --> 04:49.484
"Some." Wow.

04:49.520 --> 04:52.988
We are a team at Davis & Main.

04:53.023 --> 04:54.690
This is a team approach.

04:54.725 --> 04:56.692
You coming to us
‭as a solo practitioner...

04:56.727 --> 04:58.694
I knew there was gonna be a learning curve.

04:58.729 --> 05:01.096
But if you simply can't fit in
as part of the team...

05:01.131 --> 05:03.398
I can fit in. I... I fit in.

05:03.434 --> 05:07.002
I am here to help you and HHM win sandpiper.

05:07.037 --> 05:08.503
That's all this was about.

05:08.539 --> 05:11.006
Sandpiper's not what keeps
the lights on around here.

05:11.041 --> 05:13.408
We have clients who wouldn't
want to be associated

05:13.444 --> 05:15.544
with this kind of... this.

05:15.579 --> 05:17.612
Our image, our reputation

05:17.648 --> 05:20.615
is something we've been
carefully building for years.

05:20.651 --> 05:23.418
It's worth far more than any one case.

05:23.454 --> 05:26.455
Something like this could damage it.

05:26.490 --> 05:28.123
Suffice it to say,

05:28.158 --> 05:30.292
there's not a lot of love for
you in the room at the moment.

05:30.327 --> 05:34.129
The vote is currently two to one
to fire you for cause.

05:35.733 --> 05:38.300
However...

05:38.335 --> 05:40.469
I believe in second chances.

05:40.504 --> 05:43.772
But know this is both strike one
and strike two.

05:43.807 --> 05:48.643
Going forward, you can expect
a great deal more scrutiny.

05:48.679 --> 05:51.913
[Telephones ringing in distance]

05:53.917 --> 05:59.321
[Indistinct conversations]

05:59.356 --> 06:01.857
[Telephones ringing]

06:05.800 --> 06:09.035
[Dialing]

06:09.070 --> 06:11.838
[Ringing]

06:11.873 --> 06:15.641
Come on. Come on.

06:15.677 --> 06:17.276
Kim: Hello.

06:17.312 --> 06:19.045
You've reached the voicemail of Kim Wexler.

06:19.080 --> 06:20.613
Please leave me a message,

06:20.648 --> 06:22.715
and I'll get back to you as soon as I can.

06:22.750 --> 06:24.383
- [Beep]
- Hey, Kim. [Clears throat]

06:24.419 --> 06:26.385
I need you to call me
as soon as you can, all right?

06:26.421 --> 06:28.788
It's a time-sensitive thing, so, uh,

06:28.823 --> 06:34.393
I mean, I may have, uh, just...

06:34.429 --> 06:37.872
well, please call me
before you talk to Howard, okay?

06:38.185 --> 06:39.851
Bye.

06:39.887 --> 06:41.219
[Cellphone vibrates]

06:41.255 --> 06:42.354
Howard: It's a simple question, Kim...

06:42.364 --> 06:43.763
did you or did you not
know about this commercial?

06:43.798 --> 06:45.131
I... yes.

06:46.400 --> 06:47.500
He showed it to me.

06:47.530 --> 06:49.197
He showed it to you?

06:49.232 --> 06:50.898
Yes. A few days ago.

06:50.934 --> 06:53.601
And you didn't say anything to anyone?

06:53.636 --> 06:55.002
No. I didn't.

06:55.038 --> 06:57.405
You didn't think I deserved a heads-up?

06:57.440 --> 06:59.107
I didn't realize...

07:00.310 --> 07:02.610
at the time, ‭I didn't
think it was necessary.

07:02.645 --> 07:04.379
Well, you were wrong about that.

07:04.674 --> 07:06.541
We were caught flat-footed
in front of our co-counsel,

07:06.601 --> 07:09.568
which I don't need to tell you,
does not reflect well on HHM.

07:09.604 --> 07:11.070
Or on you.

07:18.149 --> 07:20.251
That'll be all.

07:20.350 --> 07:23.584
You can go.

07:44.417 --> 07:46.950
What are you going to do?

07:46.986 --> 07:50.921
[Sighs]

07:53.025 --> 07:55.659
Nacho: So, what do you think?

07:57.330 --> 07:59.963
I figure from here, you've got
a good bead on the place,

07:59.999 --> 08:02.232
but someone inside...
they can't pick you out.

08:02.268 --> 08:04.635
Tuco and me... that's our spot.

08:04.670 --> 08:06.036
He always sits facing out,

08:06.072 --> 08:07.838
makes it look like it's a gangster thing,

08:07.873 --> 08:10.074
but I know it's just so
he can keep an eye on his ride.

08:10.109 --> 08:13.344
Every Tuesday, ‭we're
here squaring accounts.

08:13.379 --> 08:16.013
Dealer comes in, pays what he owes.

08:16.048 --> 08:18.849
Tuco... he likes to get face-to-face.

08:18.884 --> 08:20.618
Says everything he needs to know
is written right here.

08:20.638 --> 08:22.037
Looks 'em in the eyes.

08:22.072 --> 08:23.939
Just stares, like he's
looking inside of 'em.

08:23.974 --> 08:27.676
I've seen him go like that 5, 10 minutes.

08:29.312 --> 08:33.125
[Sighs] And what does that accomplish?

08:33.159 --> 08:34.960
Calls it his lie detector.

08:34.961 --> 08:37.361
That's why these things go all day.

08:37.397 --> 08:39.964
Just the two of you? No extra muscle?

08:39.999 --> 08:42.133
Don't need it.
‭we can handle our business.

08:42.168 --> 08:43.501
Anyway, it takes hours.

08:43.535 --> 08:46.804
Collect the cash, count it, lie detector.

08:46.839 --> 08:49.440
One at a time... guy comes in,
transacts, then the next.

08:49.475 --> 08:53.477
Then, when we're done, Tuco gets
in his car, I get in mine.

08:53.513 --> 08:55.813
Boom. We go our separate ways.

08:55.848 --> 08:57.882
That is where you come in.

08:57.917 --> 09:01.185
You see him packing up...
wsssh... drive over.

09:01.220 --> 09:03.821
Pull up in the spot next to Tuco's.

09:03.856 --> 09:05.222
Pop. Head shot.

09:05.258 --> 09:07.625
Roll out. Easy.

09:07.660 --> 09:11.629
I-40 onramp is eight blocks up.

09:11.664 --> 09:13.631
You're in the wind before
anyone has time to blink.

09:13.666 --> 09:17.468
And here's the beauty...
all these, um, dealers?

09:17.503 --> 09:19.403
They know we're here, so the story is,

09:19.439 --> 09:21.572
one of them got ideas, decided to kill Tuco,

09:21.607 --> 09:23.240
get a cut of the business.

09:23.276 --> 09:26.977
Could've been any of them, as
far as the cartel's concerned.

09:27.013 --> 09:28.846
These Tuesdays of yours...

09:28.881 --> 09:31.082
day or night when you wrap it up?

09:31.117 --> 09:32.583
- Day.
- So, full daylight.

09:32.618 --> 09:34.218
- Mm-hmm.
- Plenty of traffic.

09:34.253 --> 09:36.053
How exactly do I not get seen?

09:36.089 --> 09:37.722
My car, at least.

09:37.757 --> 09:40.157
Murphy's law tells me
somebody's gonna pull a plate.

09:40.193 --> 09:42.226
Fine. Go to the yard. Buy a beater.

09:42.261 --> 09:43.728
You're gonna stay in the car.

09:43.763 --> 09:45.663
[Whistles] ‭ain't no one gonna see you.

09:45.698 --> 09:47.264
And if they do see you, so what?

09:47.300 --> 09:48.666
That's why you're perfect.

09:48.701 --> 09:51.068
You're no one. You got no connections.

09:51.104 --> 09:52.703
- You're a ghost.
- Mm-hmm.

09:52.739 --> 09:54.438
So, I pull in next to him...

09:54.474 --> 09:56.607
that assumes there's a parking spot.

09:56.642 --> 09:58.075
Our guys park next to him.

09:58.133 --> 09:59.766
They come and go from the same spot.

09:59.801 --> 10:01.334
Last one takes off, you're open.

10:01.369 --> 10:03.236
Someone comes in behind me, I'm blocked.

10:03.271 --> 10:05.505
Who's gonna pull in behind you?

10:05.540 --> 10:08.074
Well, I'm guessing someone who likes tacos.

10:08.109 --> 10:09.442
What then?

10:09.477 --> 10:11.277
What's my exit?

10:11.313 --> 10:12.912
I don't know.

10:12.948 --> 10:14.714
Get out and run.

10:14.749 --> 10:16.216
Bad knees.

10:16.251 --> 10:19.786
Look, the details...
that's what I'm paying you for.

10:19.821 --> 10:22.722
You've got a better plan, go on, tell me.

10:22.757 --> 10:24.123
I'm all ears.

10:25.227 --> 10:28.127
You sure about this?

10:28.163 --> 10:30.630
Killing your partner...

10:30.665 --> 10:35.335
[chuckles] That's a bell you don't un-ring.

10:40.442 --> 10:42.141
See this?

10:42.177 --> 10:44.911
You know how I got this?

10:44.946 --> 10:47.947
Back in '96, '97, Tuco and I

10:47.983 --> 10:50.550
were working with these bikers
out of riverside county.

10:50.585 --> 10:52.585
They were running
‭this peanut-butter crank...

10:52.621 --> 10:54.287
real shit, y'know?

10:54.322 --> 10:55.955
But cheap, and we could sell it
as fast as we got it.

10:55.991 --> 10:59.759
Anyway, ‭Tuco develops a taste for it.

10:59.794 --> 11:02.895
And crank does not bring out
the best in people.

11:02.931 --> 11:04.330
Made Tuco erratic.

11:04.366 --> 11:06.833
Our connect was a guy called Dawg Paulson.

11:06.868 --> 11:09.402
One day, ‭Tuco's settling up with Dawg.

11:09.437 --> 11:11.904
He decides ‭to put on his lie detector.

11:11.940 --> 11:14.007
Dawg's like, ‭"what the hell?" You know.

11:14.042 --> 11:15.808
Tuco just keeps staring at him.

11:15.844 --> 11:17.277
Then he goes real quiet.

11:17.312 --> 11:18.811
"You think I'm an idiot, Dawg?"

11:18.847 --> 11:20.780
He thinks dawg is supplying his competitor,

11:20.815 --> 11:22.849
trying to cut Tuco out.

11:22.884 --> 11:24.817
Dawg... he denies it.

11:26.221 --> 11:27.787
"No way! Not me!"

11:27.822 --> 11:30.757
Tuco doesn't even
‭raise his voice, but suddenly,

11:30.792 --> 11:32.692
he's got a sawed-off and...

11:32.727 --> 11:35.361
Right in Dawg's face.

11:35.397 --> 11:37.463
I was behind him.

11:38.833 --> 11:40.533
Sickest thing I ever saw, to this day.

11:40.568 --> 11:41.801
And this?

11:41.836 --> 11:43.770
A piece of dawg's skull...

11:43.805 --> 11:46.339
under the skin, a little piece of him.

11:46.374 --> 11:48.541
I tried digging it out,
but it's in there pretty good.

11:48.576 --> 11:50.810
Anyway, not the kinda thing
you go to the doctor's for.

11:50.845 --> 11:55.948
The thing about it was,
Tuco really liked Dawg.

11:55.984 --> 11:57.850
Kind of felt bad afterwards.

11:57.886 --> 12:00.687
But when he's using,
[Pops lips] Loco, crazy.

12:00.722 --> 12:02.789
There's no other way to put it.

12:02.824 --> 12:04.490
And he's using again, Crystal.

12:04.526 --> 12:06.959
Much bigger kick.

12:06.995 --> 12:09.128
So... it's like you said.

12:09.164 --> 12:13.499
If Tuco finds out about my,
y'know, independent ventures,

12:13.535 --> 12:16.336
it's gonna be Dawg all over again.

12:16.371 --> 12:19.339
It's him or me.

12:19.374 --> 12:21.507
[Sighs]

12:32.253 --> 12:34.087
There.

12:36.091 --> 12:38.524
A man with a scoped rifle
could get a clean shot.

12:40.261 --> 12:41.328
Fire a single round,

12:41.402 --> 12:43.902
disappear before anybody knew
what had happened.

12:44.299 --> 12:46.933
No witnesses. Clean egress.

12:46.968 --> 12:48.868
Pretty far.

12:50.306 --> 12:53.742
You can make that shot?

12:53.776 --> 12:56.310
Yeah. [Sighs]

12:57.413 --> 13:00.447
You saying you'll do it?

13:02.051 --> 13:04.418
50 grand?

13:04.453 --> 13:06.920
50 grand.

13:09.581 --> 13:10.963
I'll look into it.

13:13.526 --> 13:15.828
[Whirring]

13:22.448 --> 13:26.183
[Crickets chirping]

13:35.428 --> 13:36.794
[Lock disengages]

13:36.829 --> 13:37.662
Hey. Uh.

13:37.698 --> 13:39.164
Your brother isn't here, Mr. McGill.

13:39.200 --> 13:40.432
I know.

13:40.468 --> 13:42.000
Uh, he sent me to get his ink blotter.

13:42.036 --> 13:44.403
- I'll just be a second.
- Watch yourself.

13:44.438 --> 13:46.004
The floor's slick.

13:46.040 --> 13:48.273
Oh, thank you, Gesualdo.

13:48.309 --> 13:50.442
Sorry about the floor!

13:53.714 --> 13:56.582
[Sighs]

13:56.617 --> 13:59.685
Oh, no.

13:59.720 --> 14:01.420
Are you looking for Ms. Wexler?

14:01.455 --> 14:03.388
[Sighs] I guess I'm too late, huh?

14:03.424 --> 14:04.723
No, she's still here.

14:04.758 --> 14:06.792
Where?

14:06.827 --> 14:09.328
[Door opens]

14:11.465 --> 14:14.166
[Door closes]

14:22.290 --> 14:23.437
Kim.

14:26.514 --> 14:29.948
I am so, [Chuckling] So sorry.

14:29.984 --> 14:33.752
I should have told you last night.

14:33.787 --> 14:35.787
You think?

14:35.823 --> 14:37.990
I honestly thought I could fix it.

14:38.025 --> 14:41.293
I thought they'd understand
once they saw the numbers.

14:41.328 --> 14:43.462
I knew it would work, and it did.

14:43.497 --> 14:45.831
It worked. [Sighs]

14:45.866 --> 14:49.902
Howard can't just stick you in doc review

14:49.937 --> 14:51.270
because of something I did.

14:51.305 --> 14:53.071
Plus, at an ‭entirely different law firm.

14:53.107 --> 14:55.240
What the hell kind of sense does that make?!

14:55.276 --> 14:57.242
I told you this would happen.

14:57.278 --> 14:59.144
He can't blame you for this.

14:59.179 --> 15:00.812
I warned you he would.

15:02.383 --> 15:03.849
I'm talking to Howard.

15:03.884 --> 15:05.183
What?

15:05.219 --> 15:06.518
And call him a pig fucker again?

15:06.554 --> 15:07.886
Yeah, that'll help.

15:09.490 --> 15:12.858
I screwed up, you know? [Chuckling]

15:12.893 --> 15:14.192
I know that.

15:14.228 --> 15:17.296
But this... this is total bs!

15:17.331 --> 15:19.264
I'm... ‭I'm talking to him tonight!

15:19.300 --> 15:21.266
Jimmy, no. ‭you'd only make things worse.

15:21.302 --> 15:23.201
I'll explain it to him. ‭no!

15:25.306 --> 15:27.940
I'm not asking you... I'm telling you.

15:27.975 --> 15:31.043
If you go to Howard,
you and I... we're done.

15:34.648 --> 15:37.249
So, we're not done now?

15:38.986 --> 15:42.721
I need this job.

15:42.756 --> 15:44.723
And there's a weekly billing quota

15:44.758 --> 15:46.725
that I'm about 40 hours behind on,

15:46.760 --> 15:49.361
so could you please just go?

15:55.569 --> 15:58.170
I'm sorry.

16:14.388 --> 16:18.156
[Vehicle approaching]

16:18.192 --> 16:22.761
[Crickets chirping]

16:22.796 --> 16:26.365
[Engine shuts off]

16:26.400 --> 16:28.667
[Keys jingling]

16:28.702 --> 16:31.970
[Dog barking in distance]

16:42.483 --> 16:44.850
[Clattering]

16:44.885 --> 16:48.520
- [Knock on door]
- Jimmy: Chuck!

16:48.555 --> 16:51.790
- Chuck!
- [Pounding on door]

16:51.825 --> 16:53.091
Come on!

16:53.127 --> 16:56.795
[Chuckling] I'm not going away!

16:56.830 --> 17:00.198
All right, you asked for it!

17:00.234 --> 17:01.733
[Keys jingling]

17:01.769 --> 17:03.402
[Lock disengages]

17:03.437 --> 17:04.803
[Door creaks]

17:04.838 --> 17:07.204
[Keys jingling]

17:07.241 --> 17:10.275
I'm comin' in!

17:17.351 --> 17:20.252
[Chuck groans]

17:20.287 --> 17:23.121
Chuck?

17:23.156 --> 17:27.125
[Groans]

17:29.430 --> 17:31.129
Chuck?

17:31.165 --> 17:33.098
[Groans]

17:33.133 --> 17:36.601
Can you hear me?

17:36.637 --> 17:37.903
Can you talk to me?

17:37.938 --> 17:39.337
[Inhales deeply]

17:39.373 --> 17:41.406
Do you want me
‭to get you to the hospital?

17:41.442 --> 17:43.842
No. No hospitals.

17:43.877 --> 17:47.145
I'll... I'll be all right.

17:47.181 --> 17:53.185
Get some water, please.

17:53.220 --> 17:55.821
[Sighs]

17:55.856 --> 17:59.391
[Crickets chirping]

18:01.795 --> 18:04.830
[Jimmy sighs]

18:04.865 --> 18:09.134
[Groans]

18:13.640 --> 18:18.510
Extra protection here.

18:22.416 --> 18:25.751
Ohh.

18:27.354 --> 18:29.020
[Sighs, groans]

18:29.056 --> 18:31.289
Here. You know what?

18:31.325 --> 18:32.691
Sit up.

18:32.726 --> 18:34.960
- Aah!
- Can you sit?

18:34.995 --> 18:37.796
- Ow.
- All right. [Sighs]

18:37.831 --> 18:39.898
Okay. All right.

18:39.933 --> 18:41.433
Here.

18:44.538 --> 18:46.138
Mm.

18:53.247 --> 18:56.414
[Sighs]

18:58.018 --> 19:01.520
Mm.

19:02.589 --> 19:06.091
[Sighs]

19:19.940 --> 19:24.209
[Sighs]

19:28.115 --> 19:32.551
Lawson: That's the Armalite AR-50...

19:32.586 --> 19:36.755
state of the art,
‭accurate to 2,400 meters.

19:36.790 --> 19:39.057
I got the Leupold Mark 4 on it now,

19:39.092 --> 19:42.194
but I can always upgrade you
to a Schmidt & Bender.

19:42.229 --> 19:44.462
Single shot, bolt.

19:44.498 --> 19:47.065
Simple, effective, reliable.

19:47.100 --> 19:49.801
It fires the .50-caliber BMG...

19:49.837 --> 19:53.071
very effective against
soft targets in light cover...

19:53.106 --> 19:55.807
behind cars, ‭small-diameter
trees, and such.

19:55.843 --> 19:58.109
As always, I've gone to the trouble

19:58.145 --> 20:00.412
of grinding down the serial number.

20:00.447 --> 20:03.148
Well, unless you
‭ground a hole clean through,

20:03.183 --> 20:04.482
acid will recover it.

20:04.518 --> 20:06.218
Well, that would be true,

20:06.253 --> 20:07.752
but I follow up with a pass

20:07.788 --> 20:09.788
through ‭a random-stipple machine press.

20:09.823 --> 20:12.257
Hides the patterns in the metal density.

20:12.292 --> 20:14.659
Should throw off your x-ray diffraction

20:14.695 --> 20:16.795
and some other higher-end methods.

20:16.830 --> 20:19.664
Nothing's perfect, of course,
but this is close.

20:19.700 --> 20:21.099
Mm.

20:21.134 --> 20:24.769
Looks like a hernia with a scope on it.

20:24.805 --> 20:26.171
34 pounds,

20:26.206 --> 20:30.909
not including your bipod,
which adds some heft.

20:30.944 --> 20:33.411
Too much gun.

20:33.447 --> 20:36.815
For most applications,
I would tend to agree.

20:36.850 --> 20:41.686
SR-25 match rifle... Eugene
Stoner design, semi-auto.

20:41.722 --> 20:43.755
That's about 11 pounds there.

20:43.790 --> 20:46.758
Not quite the range
or the punch of the AR-50,

20:46.793 --> 20:49.494
but you're still talking about a .5 M.O.A.

20:49.529 --> 20:51.630
At well past 1,000 meters.

20:51.665 --> 20:53.265
I've heard they're prone to jam.

20:53.300 --> 20:55.433
Well, it's been known
to happen in the field,

20:55.469 --> 20:59.004
but there's not a semi-auto
built can boast it never jams.

20:59.039 --> 21:02.173
If that's a concern,
you ought to stick to bolts.

21:02.209 --> 21:05.010
Good bolt-action rifle... if you jammed it,

21:05.045 --> 21:07.679
I'd wager ‭you were setting out to do so.

21:07.714 --> 21:12.851
Which brings us to the M40...

21:12.886 --> 21:15.553
tried and true, battle-tested.

21:15.589 --> 21:20.492
Essentially, the same rifle used
by marine snipers since 1966.

21:20.527 --> 21:24.062
It's light, accurate, good for soft targets

21:24.097 --> 21:26.498
in the 800 to 1,2000-meter range.

21:29.703 --> 21:32.070
You seem to know this one.

21:32.105 --> 21:33.405
Oh, yeah.

21:33.440 --> 21:35.674
You could say that.

21:35.709 --> 21:38.710
That's the a1 model.

21:38.745 --> 21:41.746
There's not much change from the original.

21:41.782 --> 21:44.349
Biggest difference is the stock...

21:44.384 --> 21:46.818
it's fiberglass instead of wood.

21:46.853 --> 21:49.321
It changed it over in 1970 or so.

21:49.356 --> 21:53.325
Good. Wood warped like hell.

21:53.360 --> 21:56.594
You get it wet,
‭you put it in the sun... gone.

21:57.698 --> 22:00.699
Somebody probably
‭should've figured that out

22:00.734 --> 22:03.501
before they sent it into a damn jungle.

22:03.537 --> 22:09.140
Yeah. Probably.

22:12.779 --> 22:15.013
If these aren't to your liking,

22:15.048 --> 22:17.515
I could get my hands on a few more.

22:17.551 --> 22:18.750
No.

22:18.785 --> 22:20.952
I've changed my mind.

22:20.988 --> 22:22.220
Thank you.

22:22.255 --> 22:25.323
I don't need anything at this time.

22:26.426 --> 22:27.625
For your trouble.

22:27.661 --> 22:29.094
Oh, it's no trouble.

22:29.129 --> 22:31.363
I make my living on repeat business.

22:31.398 --> 22:34.733
When you need what I'm offering,
you know how to find me.

22:48.909 --> 22:55.548
[Birds chirping, blanket crinkling]

22:55.583 --> 22:57.583
[Sighs]

23:00.049 --> 23:01.919
[Breathes deeply]

23:08.591 --> 23:10.724
You're still here.

23:10.759 --> 23:14.227
Jimmy: Yeah, I'm still here.

23:14.263 --> 23:15.495
Mm.

23:15.531 --> 23:17.898
[Breathes deeply]

23:17.933 --> 23:20.500
Ohh.

23:20.536 --> 23:23.036
Ohh.

23:23.072 --> 23:24.504
Oh.

23:24.540 --> 23:27.007
[Sighs]

23:30.349 --> 23:32.161
Did you get any sleep?

23:32.243 --> 23:34.910
- Some.
- Mm.

23:34.944 --> 23:36.744
Enough.

23:36.779 --> 23:39.013
- [Sighs]
- How you feeling?

23:39.048 --> 23:40.248
[Sighs]

23:40.283 --> 23:42.383
I could use some tea.

23:46.589 --> 23:49.490
Thanks.

23:57.600 --> 24:00.134
[Spoon clatters]

24:00.170 --> 24:03.304
[Both sigh]

24:05.742 --> 24:07.142
- Ohh.
- You scared me last night.

24:07.208 --> 24:09.493
Yeah. Happens sometimes.

24:09.749 --> 24:10.831
[Inhales deeply]

24:10.919 --> 24:12.789
Sometimes, I overdo it... that's all.

24:13.246 --> 24:15.775
It passes. [Inhales deeply]

24:15.818 --> 24:19.620
Going into the office really
takes it out of you, doesn't it?

24:19.656 --> 24:21.455
If I stay too long, yeah.

24:21.491 --> 24:23.558
Guess it's hard not to stay.

24:23.593 --> 24:26.994
There's so many important things
for you to do there...

24:27.030 --> 24:29.597
like, you know, stick it to Kim Wexler.

24:29.632 --> 24:31.999
What did I do to Kim Wexler?

24:32.035 --> 24:35.102
She's back in the cornfield, isn't she?

24:35.138 --> 24:37.505
I didn't do anything to Kim.

24:37.540 --> 24:41.309
I mean, I was present, yes.

24:41.344 --> 24:42.743
But management of personnel...

24:42.779 --> 24:44.645
those decisions are all Howard's.

24:44.681 --> 24:46.180
[Chuckles] That is rich.

24:46.216 --> 24:46.915
But tell me,

24:46.953 --> 24:48.687
when Howard was makin'
his "management decisions,"

24:49.619 --> 24:52.320
was he sitting on your knee
with your arm up his ass?

24:52.355 --> 24:55.290
Hey, can he talk while
you drink a glass of water?

24:55.346 --> 24:56.545
That's uncalled-for.

24:56.859 --> 24:58.593
And if Howard were my puppet,

24:58.628 --> 25:01.762
he certainly wouldn't have
recommended you to Davis & Main.

25:01.798 --> 25:03.864
Actually, I'm sure it was Kim Wexler

25:03.900 --> 25:05.766
who talked him into doing that.

25:05.802 --> 25:06.801
Hence his anger.

25:06.892 --> 25:08.157
Don't punish Kim.

25:08.538 --> 25:11.005
If you're mad at me, take it out on me.

25:11.040 --> 25:13.207
- [Cup clinks]
- [Clears throat]

25:13.243 --> 25:15.943
I know you like to think

25:15.979 --> 25:17.646
the world revolves around you, Jimmy,

25:17.715 --> 25:20.115
but this has nothing to do with you.

25:20.151 --> 25:23.285
Kim had a responsibility
to Hamlin, Hamlin, McGill.

25:23.321 --> 25:25.821
She should have been looking out
for her firm's interests.

25:25.856 --> 25:28.290
Not letting us know what
you were up to was her mistake.

25:28.326 --> 25:29.725
Oh, come on.

25:29.760 --> 25:31.727
You can't be pissed off at her about this.

25:31.762 --> 25:32.995
I'm not.

25:33.030 --> 25:34.229
[Chuckling] Howard is.

25:34.265 --> 25:35.497
And why shouldn't he be?

25:35.533 --> 25:37.566
Because she didn't know.

25:37.602 --> 25:41.136
She didn't know ‭I was
gonna air the commercial.

25:41.172 --> 25:43.305
She didn't know
‭I hadn't gotten it approved.

25:43.341 --> 25:44.840
She just... she didn't know.

25:45.999 --> 25:47.199
[Sighs]

25:47.234 --> 25:48.467
[Newspaper thuds]

25:48.502 --> 25:49.701
I see.

25:49.737 --> 25:50.769
So, she didn't know

25:50.832 --> 25:53.966
there was anything that
she was supposed to tell Howard.

25:54.002 --> 25:55.801
As far as she was concerned,

25:55.837 --> 25:57.870
Cliff Main was already looped in.

25:57.906 --> 26:00.473
You told her he was?

26:00.508 --> 26:01.874
I implied it.

26:01.910 --> 26:03.776
So it's on me, not her.

26:03.811 --> 26:05.044
[Sighs]

26:05.079 --> 26:06.913
[Engine starts in distance]

26:09.117 --> 26:11.584
She didn't say anything to us about that.

26:11.619 --> 26:13.085
Well, she wouldn't.

26:13.121 --> 26:15.955
Sh-she wouldn't want to make me look bad.

26:15.990 --> 26:19.659
You have to admit this shows
a lack of judgment on her part.

26:19.694 --> 26:20.927
She knows you.

26:20.929 --> 26:21.962
She should have known better.

26:22.044 --> 26:23.477
You are such an asshole.

26:23.512 --> 26:25.145
Why?

26:25.181 --> 26:27.414
For pointing out that her one
mistake was believing in you?

26:27.450 --> 26:29.984
For Christ's sake, can we get
some perspective here?

26:30.019 --> 26:31.819
It was a simple, little commercial.

26:31.854 --> 26:33.354
It aired once... that's all.

26:33.389 --> 26:35.155
And can I remind you... it worked.

26:35.191 --> 26:36.490
It worked like a dream.

26:36.525 --> 26:38.258
See, that's your problem, Jimmy...

26:38.294 --> 26:40.160
thinking the ends justify the means.

26:40.196 --> 26:43.063
And you're forever shocked when
it all blows up in your face.

26:43.099 --> 26:44.331
[Scoffs]

26:44.367 --> 26:45.866
What did I do that was so wrong?

26:45.901 --> 26:47.701
[Sighs] You broke the rules.

26:48.897 --> 26:51.431
‭You turned Kim into your accessory.

26:51.462 --> 26:54.029
You embarrassed Howard, who...
God help him...

26:54.065 --> 26:56.565
inexplicably vouched for
you with Cliff Main!

26:56.601 --> 26:58.734
You made Cliff and his
partners look like schmucks!

26:58.769 --> 27:00.302
Shall I go on?!

27:00.338 --> 27:05.274
How he hasn't fired you for this
positively mystifies me.

27:05.309 --> 27:06.709
"Perspective."

27:06.744 --> 27:08.644
You want perspective?

27:08.679 --> 27:10.279
I'll give you mine...

27:10.314 --> 27:12.915
You're my brother and I love you,

27:12.950 --> 27:15.017
but you're like an alcoholic

27:15.029 --> 27:16.495
who refuses to admit he's got a problem.

27:16.530 --> 27:19.498
Now someone's given you
the keys to the school bus,

27:19.533 --> 27:22.334
and I'm not gonna let you
drive it off a cliff!

27:22.369 --> 27:24.736
Now, can we just get down
to brass tacks here?

27:24.772 --> 27:27.506
What can I do to put Kim
back where she belongs, huh?

27:27.541 --> 27:29.741
What... you want me to quit Davis & Main?

27:29.777 --> 27:31.276
That's fine.

27:31.312 --> 27:32.878
I... I never wanted that job
in the first place.

27:32.913 --> 27:34.446
I can't get through to you.

27:34.481 --> 27:37.015
Life is not one big game
of "let's make a deal"!

27:37.051 --> 27:39.117
Yes, it is! ‭[Chuckles] I'm Monty Hall!

27:39.153 --> 27:40.852
What's behind door number two?

27:40.888 --> 27:42.220
What'll it take, huh?!

27:42.256 --> 27:44.122
You want me to quit being a lawyer?

27:44.158 --> 27:45.390
[Scoffs]

27:45.426 --> 27:47.893
Ju... a chimp with a machine gun...

27:47.928 --> 27:49.761
That's me, right, huh?!

27:49.797 --> 27:51.463
So, what do you say?

27:51.498 --> 27:53.799
You help Kim, I quit the law.

27:53.834 --> 27:56.301
- Is that a deal?
- ‭I didn't say that.

27:56.337 --> 27:58.737
No, you didn't say it, but
that's what you want, right?!

27:58.772 --> 28:01.239
That's why you put the screws
to Kim in the first place...

28:01.275 --> 28:02.774
to squeeze me!

28:02.810 --> 28:04.109
I didn't say that,
‭and I would never say that!

28:04.144 --> 28:05.944
Why not?!

28:05.979 --> 28:09.147
Because if I were impeding the
career of one of my employees

28:09.183 --> 28:11.083
for the purpose of compelling you

28:11.118 --> 28:14.252
to do something against your
will, that would be extortion.

28:14.288 --> 28:15.954
Yeah. ‭It would. [Chuckles]

28:15.989 --> 28:17.322
So?

28:17.358 --> 28:19.591
You gonna extort me, Chuck?

28:19.626 --> 28:21.760
It's a lead-pipe cinch
you'd get away with it.

28:21.795 --> 28:23.261
I'm not gonna tell anyone.

28:23.297 --> 28:25.464
It's real easy... you just
set things right for Kim.

28:25.499 --> 28:27.666
You get her back in her office,
out of doc review...

28:27.701 --> 28:32.070
everything back to normal,
and I quit the law for good.

28:32.106 --> 28:34.673
No more Jimmy McGill, esquire... poof!

28:34.708 --> 28:36.675
Like he never even existed.

28:36.710 --> 28:38.510
Wow.

28:38.545 --> 28:40.345
Wow.

28:40.381 --> 28:42.514
But I need to hear the words
come out of your mouth, okay?

28:42.549 --> 28:43.549
[Scoffs] ‭You're a man of your word.

28:43.572 --> 28:45.139
You're an upstanding man, right?

28:45.174 --> 28:47.130
- For God's sake, Jimmy.
- Come on, Chuck!

28:47.233 --> 28:48.432
Extort me!

28:48.467 --> 28:50.501
Say "quit," and I will quit,

28:50.536 --> 28:53.103
but I need to hear it from your mouth!

28:53.139 --> 28:55.172
You want me to commit a felony...

28:55.207 --> 28:57.374
Because that's what you'd do, right?

28:57.410 --> 29:00.911
Because you want to believe that
deep down, I'm some hypocrite!

29:00.946 --> 29:02.179
Let's find out.

29:02.214 --> 29:03.714
Come on down, Chuck!

29:03.749 --> 29:05.883
Roll around in the dirt with me!

29:05.918 --> 29:08.018
All your dreams will come true!

29:08.054 --> 29:11.155
Go on! Do it! Go on!

29:12.758 --> 29:16.226
I am not the bad guy here.

29:16.262 --> 29:18.062
You don't want to be a lawyer...

29:18.097 --> 29:20.597
that's between you
‭and the New Mexico State Bar.

29:20.633 --> 29:22.933
You want to quit Davis & Main? Be my guest!

29:22.968 --> 29:25.769
You clearly don't need any help
from me to tank your career.

29:25.818 --> 29:27.573
You're doing just fine on your own.

29:27.973 --> 29:29.440
[Inhales deeply]

29:29.475 --> 29:32.976
Speaking of which, it's an
hour's drive to Santa Fe.

29:33.012 --> 29:35.245
Even iyou leave right now,

29:35.281 --> 29:38.215
you're still gonna be at least
20 minutes late for work...

29:38.250 --> 29:41.752
another feather in your cap
with Clifford Main.

29:41.787 --> 29:45.522
[Clock ticking]

29:50.696 --> 29:54.264
[Chuck sighs]

29:54.300 --> 29:56.800
[Door creaks]

30:04.510 --> 30:06.276
So?

30:08.685 --> 30:10.986
I'm not gonna do it.

30:11.002 --> 30:12.536
What... ‭are you negotiating now?

30:12.559 --> 30:15.560
No amount of money makes this
a good idea... for you.

30:15.913 --> 30:18.213
Look, man, ‭I told you that I'm not...

30:18.248 --> 30:21.817
No, it's a bad move because it
doesn't solve your real problem.

30:21.852 --> 30:23.752
My real problem? What's that?

30:23.787 --> 30:25.887
[Inhales deeply] It's not Tuco.

30:25.923 --> 30:28.056
It's keeping a secret.

30:28.092 --> 30:31.993
A dead Tuco ‭draws salamancas like flies.

30:32.029 --> 30:35.097
The cartel noses into the business,

30:35.132 --> 30:36.932
looks for who hit one of theirs.

30:36.967 --> 30:39.334
You gonna be able to keep your secrets then?

30:39.370 --> 30:41.603
Something's got to give.

30:41.638 --> 30:45.240
With you, without you... I don't care.

30:45.275 --> 30:48.176
But something's gonna happen.

30:48.212 --> 30:49.978
You said it yourself.

30:50.013 --> 30:54.082
You don't need him dead...
you need him to go away.

30:54.118 --> 30:55.317
You mean snitch?

30:55.352 --> 30:56.852
Man, I drop a dime on Tuco,

30:56.887 --> 30:58.854
who do you think the cartel looks at?

30:58.889 --> 31:00.022
Me.

31:00.033 --> 31:01.333
And if I call the cops,
I get picked up, too.

31:01.368 --> 31:03.068
I'm what you call a known associate.

31:03.103 --> 31:04.602
So I'm locked up with Tuco,

31:04.638 --> 31:06.938
who's looking for the guy
that put him there.

31:06.974 --> 31:08.440
Tell me how that helps me.

31:08.475 --> 31:11.009
You won't have to talk to the cops.

31:11.044 --> 31:13.278
You won't have to do any time.

31:13.313 --> 31:17.282
There's no killing, but your Tuco problem?

31:17.317 --> 31:19.751
It goes away.

31:31.358 --> 31:34.099
[Wind rushing]

31:35.734 --> 31:39.736
[Wings flapping]

31:39.772 --> 31:43.507
["Muneca de Jalisco" plays in background]

32:28.378 --> 32:29.558
It's all there.

32:29.593 --> 32:30.859
Shh.

32:30.895 --> 32:34.196
Let the man count.

32:34.231 --> 32:37.700
[Music continues]

32:39.770 --> 32:43.872
We're good.

32:47.945 --> 32:52.681
So, uh... till next time, huh?

32:52.717 --> 32:57.720
[Music continues]

33:05.896 --> 33:08.030
Tuco.

33:08.065 --> 33:13.302
[Music continues]

33:21.977 --> 33:23.978
Okay.

33:23.998 --> 33:25.165
Go.

33:25.172 --> 33:26.572
Okay.

33:26.607 --> 33:30.809
I'll, uh... ‭I'll see you next week, Tuco.

33:30.845 --> 33:32.544
Nacho.

33:32.580 --> 33:35.214
Yeah, see you, Domingo.

33:38.444 --> 33:39.852
Nacho: He's got good numbers.

33:40.929 --> 33:42.929
He's hustlin'.

33:42.965 --> 33:46.266
What do you think?

33:46.301 --> 33:47.934
Solid?

33:49.004 --> 33:52.105
[Inhales sharply]

33:52.141 --> 33:55.876
[Music continues]

34:06.722 --> 34:10.489
[Coins clatter]

34:18.367 --> 34:21.768
Uh, uh, y-yes, I would like
to report a fight going on

34:21.804 --> 34:23.670
at the El Michoacano Restaurant

34:23.705 --> 34:26.206
in the 5000 block of the Isleta Boulevard.

34:26.241 --> 34:29.376
There's a man threatening
another man with a gun.

34:29.411 --> 34:32.579
It [Chuckles] Looks to be
some sort of gang thing.

34:33.581 --> 34:35.482
Oh, uh, uh, uh, sorry.

34:35.516 --> 34:37.384
I... I... I'm a passerby.

34:37.418 --> 34:39.953
I... I don't want to get involved.

34:39.987 --> 34:44.824
[Coins clinking]

34:46.895 --> 34:49.396
[Engine revs]

35:10.252 --> 35:11.818
["El Querreque" plays in background]

35:11.854 --> 35:13.987
The fuck?

35:14.022 --> 35:15.522
Did you see that?

35:15.557 --> 35:16.756
See what?

35:16.792 --> 35:20.594
That old man just hit my car.

35:25.934 --> 35:29.069
[Music continues]

35:29.104 --> 35:32.072
[Grill sizzling]

35:33.657 --> 35:36.158
[Door closes]

35:36.676 --> 35:39.710
Hey.

35:39.745 --> 35:40.846
[Inhales deeply]

35:40.886 --> 35:42.719
- Hello.
- Oh. Hmm.

35:43.749 --> 35:45.583
Well, let me see.

35:45.618 --> 35:47.151
Um...

35:47.186 --> 35:50.221
Give me the number four,
the pollo, por favor.

35:50.256 --> 35:52.523
- That's to go.
- Yes, sir.

35:52.558 --> 35:54.225
Tuco: Hey, you.

35:54.260 --> 35:55.493
Hey, gramps.

35:55.528 --> 35:57.561
You just hit my car.

35:57.597 --> 35:59.997
Uh, you're talking to me?

36:00.032 --> 36:01.398
[Laughs]

36:01.434 --> 36:03.601
Check out Mr. Magoo here.

36:03.636 --> 36:05.369
Uh, y-yes, sir.

36:05.404 --> 36:09.373
You see that car that you parked
your piece of shit next to?

36:09.408 --> 36:10.708
That's mine.

36:10.743 --> 36:13.043
You just ran into it.

36:13.079 --> 36:14.578
No, I don't think I did.

36:14.614 --> 36:16.013
You calling me a liar?

36:16.048 --> 36:17.548
Oh.

36:17.583 --> 36:19.850
Uh, no.

36:19.886 --> 36:23.020
Hey. I saw it, too.

36:23.055 --> 36:24.855
You gonna stand here and deny it?

36:24.891 --> 36:27.858
Um, guys, um, I... I don't
know what to tell you.

36:27.894 --> 36:30.427
I'm not aware ‭of hitting anyone's car,

36:30.463 --> 36:33.230
but if I did... I apologize.

36:33.266 --> 36:36.800
- So...
- $6.33.

36:37.904 --> 36:40.070
Mm.

36:40.106 --> 36:42.306
[Music continues]

36:42.341 --> 36:44.475
You keep the change.

36:44.935 --> 36:45.968
Thank you.

36:46.055 --> 36:47.988
Excuse me.

36:48.023 --> 36:50.457
[Music continues]

36:50.493 --> 36:52.493
[Bell jingles]

36:54.497 --> 36:56.363
Don't you walk away from me.

36:56.398 --> 36:58.966
Hey, pops. You better listen to the man.

36:59.001 --> 37:00.334
Come on, guys.

37:00.369 --> 37:02.870
Let's just keep things friendly, all right?

37:02.905 --> 37:04.371
I ain't your friend.

37:05.249 --> 37:06.515
Look!

37:06.551 --> 37:08.818
You see that? You... you did that.

37:08.853 --> 37:10.953
Oh, come on. That'll buff right out.

37:13.057 --> 37:15.925
You're gonna make this all right.

37:15.960 --> 37:18.761
You're not leaving until you do.

37:18.796 --> 37:20.863
Fine. You got a pen?

37:20.898 --> 37:22.264
A pen.

37:22.300 --> 37:25.468
A pen... we'll exchange
information, insurance.

37:25.535 --> 37:26.536
I have very good coverage.

37:26.577 --> 37:28.710
They'll take care of this.

37:29.561 --> 37:32.762
I'm not messing around with insurance, ése.

37:32.797 --> 37:34.364
Cash.

37:34.399 --> 37:37.467
[Scoffs] Listen, I'm willing
to accept responsibility,

37:37.502 --> 37:39.068
but if you're not going through insurance,

37:39.104 --> 37:42.872
then I have maybe 20,
30 bucks on me... that's all.

37:42.907 --> 37:44.741
Kay, now you're lying to me.

37:44.776 --> 37:47.643
I saw your wallet.
You got plenty in there.

37:48.608 --> 37:50.007
Take it out.

37:50.043 --> 37:53.844
Let's look together, jog your memory.

37:53.880 --> 37:55.313
You heard him.

37:55.348 --> 37:57.515
Take out the wallet.

37:57.550 --> 37:59.717
I just cashed my social security check.

37:59.752 --> 38:01.486
It's all I have till the end of the month,

38:01.546 --> 38:03.313
and I am not giving it to you.

38:03.923 --> 38:05.856
[Laughs]

38:05.892 --> 38:06.992
You're not?

38:07.190 --> 38:08.857
I offered to do this the right way.

38:09.361 --> 38:11.494
If you can't accept that,
then I can't help you.

38:11.530 --> 38:12.063
[Keys jingling]

38:12.078 --> 38:13.778
Aw, come on, guys.

38:13.813 --> 38:15.212
[Sighs]

38:15.248 --> 38:17.948
I'm gonna make this real simple for you.

38:17.984 --> 38:23.421
Give me your wallet, and maybe
you walk away from this.

38:25.491 --> 38:29.727
I'm not giving you a damn thing.

38:31.327 --> 38:32.960
Nah, homes.

38:32.996 --> 38:35.129
Give me your wallet.

38:35.198 --> 38:37.031
Let's just stay calm here.

38:37.066 --> 38:39.567
[Laughs] You see me sweating, bitch?

38:39.602 --> 38:42.970
- Wallet.
- ‭[Sighs]

38:43.005 --> 38:45.039
Wallet.

38:45.074 --> 38:48.876
♪

38:48.911 --> 38:51.378
Wallet.

38:51.414 --> 38:55.616
♪

39:05.027 --> 39:08.996
- There's like $400 here.
- [Siren wailing in distance]

39:09.031 --> 39:12.266
You got some crazy lip on you, old man.

39:12.301 --> 39:14.335
Your life worth 400 bucks?

39:14.402 --> 39:16.535
Hey, Tuco, time to bounce.

39:16.570 --> 39:19.538
Yeah, go. Go.

39:19.573 --> 39:21.774
[Keys jingling]

39:25.346 --> 39:28.147
[Engine starts]

39:28.182 --> 39:32.751
You're... one lucky old man.

39:32.787 --> 39:34.920
What the hell? Leggo!

39:34.955 --> 39:36.455
Let go!

39:36.490 --> 39:38.223
[Both grunting]

39:38.259 --> 39:41.060
Let...Let... let go!

39:41.095 --> 39:42.628
[Siren wailing]

39:42.663 --> 39:44.229
Let go!

39:44.265 --> 39:45.464
‭Let go!

39:45.499 --> 39:48.801
Let go!

39:48.836 --> 39:51.470
[Dripping blood echoes]

39:51.505 --> 39:54.105
[Distorted warbling]

40:00.514 --> 40:02.581
[Sirens wailing]

40:02.616 --> 40:04.583
[Tires screech]

40:04.618 --> 40:06.618
Let me see your hands!

40:06.654 --> 40:09.955
Hands up! Now!

40:09.990 --> 40:12.091
On the ground!

40:12.126 --> 40:14.493
That all you got?

40:14.528 --> 40:17.362
Get on the ground!

40:17.398 --> 40:19.264
[Laughs]

40:19.300 --> 40:20.499
[Punch echoes]

40:20.534 --> 40:24.303
[Distorted warbling]

40:32.480 --> 40:36.215
[Warbling fades]

40:39.854 --> 40:42.354
[Gearshift clicks]

40:43.491 --> 40:45.057
[Door creaks]

40:45.092 --> 40:48.861
[Wind whistling]

41:15.329 --> 41:17.395
Wow.

41:17.431 --> 41:21.299
Look at you.

41:21.335 --> 41:24.903
Are you gonna have to testify?

41:24.938 --> 41:29.309
The cops witnessed him
in the commission of a felony.

41:29.405 --> 41:31.772
My wallet in his pocket.

41:31.807 --> 41:35.442
Add the gun... ‭he gets a 5 to 10 stretch.

41:40.049 --> 41:41.382
$25,000.

41:41.417 --> 41:44.918
You definitely earned it.

41:44.954 --> 41:47.888
Still, you coulda gotten twice as much

41:47.923 --> 41:49.456
for 1/10 the hassle.

41:49.492 --> 41:52.192
You woulda done the world a favor.

41:52.228 --> 41:55.129
You wouldn't look like someone
took a lead pipe to your face.

41:55.164 --> 41:59.400
Plus, when Tuco gets out,
maybe he comes looking for you.

41:59.435 --> 42:01.068
Get to the point.

42:01.103 --> 42:05.572
Just saying... you went a long
way to not pull that trigger.

42:07.977 --> 42:10.144
Why?

42:10.179 --> 42:13.947
[Wind rushing]

42:31.934 --> 42:33.434
[Door creaks]

42:37.540 --> 42:40.040
[Car door creaks shut]

